# Expected Conclusion

Students should understand:

✔ Soft Link = Shortcut to original file

✔ Hard Link = Another name for the same file

✔ Soft Link → Different inode number

✔ Hard Link → Same inode number

✔ Soft Link breaks when original file is deleted

✔ Hard Link continues to work even after original file is deleted

✔ Inode stores metadata about files such as permissions, ownership, size, timestamps, and disk location.
